{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"75a38423-e05f-459c-a06e-2164530f45bc","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the VSTest switches become MTP extensions passed after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n| VSTest flag | MTP equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n`--filter` stays on the `dotnet test` side (before `--`) and is translated automatically.\n\nYou'll also need to add these NuGet packages to your test project:\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"44642e90-4d65-4c9e-acd2-b88bcfc3481c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET tooling ã I don't need to explore the repo for this.\n\nLet me translate each flag:\n\n1. `dotnet test` ã `dotnet test` (still works, but MTP uses different CLI args)\n2. `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` ã `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` (same, but MTP uses `--treenode-filter` for the native runner, though `dotnet test` integration may still support `--filter`)\n\n\n3. `--logger trx` ã `--report-trx`\n4. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` ã `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n5. `--blame-crash` ã `--crashdump`\n6. `--blame-hang` ã `--hangdump`\n\nThe mapping depends on whether they're running through `dotnet test` (which has some compatibility) or directly via the MTP native runner.\n\nWith .NET 8 and MTP, when using `dotnet test`, you pass MTP-specific arguments after `--` to separate them from the dotnet test arguments. The recommended pattern is something like `dotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" -- --report` to combine both the dotnet test filters and MTP-specific options.\n\nBut I'm realizing the filter syntax differs between `dotnet test` and MTP directlyã`dotnet test` uses `--filter` while MTP uses `--treenode-filter` with a different syntax. I need to think through whether `dotnet test` translates the filter automatically or if I should be using the MTP syntax directly when passing arguments after `--`.\n\nAlso, these reporting and diagnostic features aren't built into MTP by defaultãthey require specific NuGet extensions like `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for TRX output, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` for coverage, and similar packages for crash and hang dumps.","outputTokens":1233,"requestId":"4819:14859A:31AB610:3642755:69FBE338"},"id":"440d0e6e-7672-4780-8751-8712ea585337","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:56:46.493Z","parentId":"786bfc08-47f7-4f2a-bb16-fd9f19cea6cb"}
